}, {\"ngram\": \"an open letter\", \"from\": 639, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"clear plan\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 726}, {\"ngram\": \"acrossGovernmentwith concrete steps\", \"from\": 732, \"to\": 767}, {\"ngram\": \"change\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 778}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whiston, who stormed to women's SM8 200m individual medley gold, will soon return to her job as a teaching assistant for children with special needs and as a communicator for the deaf, and also works as a swimming instructor.\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 1007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"score\": 0.9999999997971827, \"rank\": 1.2310253222161583e-10, \"text\": \"Whiston\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\"}, {\"begin\": 818, \"end\": 840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 0.9999711346650378, \"rank\": 2.8866168039882347e-05, \"text\": \"200m individual medley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_2004_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"score\": 0.9999999999868123, \"rank\": 9.382268128991527e-12, \"text\": \"gold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her job\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"a teaching assistant\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 898}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"special needs\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"a communicator\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 952}, {\"ngram\": \"the deaf\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"a swimming instructor\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking at St Pancras station, freshly disembarked from theEurostar, she said: \\\"Some of the children I work with have physical impairments and parents come up to me at school and they are like, 'So you can do it!'.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"St Pancras station\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1039}, {\"ngram\": \"theEurostar\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1077}, {\"ngram\": \"the children\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"physical impairments\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1148}, {\"ngram\": \"parents\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"school\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1184}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am like, yeah, it just might not be the direct route, but we will get there in the end, whether it means we take a couple of steps backwards to go forwards, but we will get there eventually.\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1419, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the direct route\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"a couple\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1350}, {\"ngram\": \"steps\", \"from\": 1354, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Definitely, for me, it's something that needs to change and it will change, because we will make sure it does.\", \"from\": 1421, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1456}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We will never be equal, because you can not possibly be equal, but you should always get the same opportunities.\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same opportunities\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1646}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sometimes we might need extra support, but that's OK. Everyone needs to be able to achieve their full potential, no matter what it takes, and there is millions of children out there that have that potential.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1857, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"extra support\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1687}, {\"ngram\": \"Everyone\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"their full potential\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1761}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1809}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"that potential\", \"from\": 1842, \"to\": 1856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They just have not been reached yet.\\\"\", \"from\": 1859, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A ParalympicsGB study found only one in four disabled children regularly took part in school sport.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A ParalympicsGB study\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1920}, {\"ngram\": \"only one in four disabled children\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1981}, {\"ngram\": \"school sport\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 1997}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The open letter read: \\\"As Paralympians, and as disabled people, we are more determined than ever to use this platform to do all we can to prevent the next generation of children being left on the sidelines in the birthplace of the Paralympic movement.\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2231, \"end\": 2250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic movement\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Paralympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The open letter\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2015}, {\"ngram\": \"Paralympians\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2038}, {\"ngram\": \"disabled people\", \"from\": 2047, \"to\": 2062}, {\"ngram\": \"this platform\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"the next generation\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2165}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2177}, {\"ngram\": \"the sidelines\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"the birthplace\", \"from\": 2209, \"to\": 2223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There are 1.5 million disabled children - 15 per cent of the school population - and it is shocking that such a large number of young people do not have the chance to participate in sport and develop and grow as a result.\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2475, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"1.5 million disabled children\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2293}, {\"ngram\": \"15 per cent\", \"from\": 2296, \"to\": 2307}, {\"ngram\": \"the school population\", \"from\": 2311, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"such a large number\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2378}, {\"ngram\": \"young people\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2417}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2441}, {\"ngram\": \"a result\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2474}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are heartened by your support for the Equal Play campaign and we are asking you to act now to ensure every child has the same access to PE at school.\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2617, \"end\": 2619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"score\": 0.9999999999431566, \"rank\": 5.5245450016798584e-11, \"text\": \"PE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your support\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2510}, {\"ngram\": \"the Equal Play campaign\", \"from\": 2515, \"to\": 2538}, {\"ngram\": \"every child\", \"from\": 2582, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the same access\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2613}, {\"ngram\": \"school\", \"from\": 2623, \"to\": 2629}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Your Government has a unique opportunity to shift the dial so that by the Los Angeles 2028 Paralympic Games, no disabled child faces this discrimination.\\\"\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2705, \"end\": 2721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles 2028\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2028_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Your Government\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2646}, {\"ngram\": \"a unique opportunity\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2671}, {\"ngram\": \"the dial\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"no disabled child\", \"from\": 2740, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"this discrimination\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 2783}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The letter calls for better training and tools for teachers, more emphasis on PE in the curriculum and a push to increase the number of disabled people entering the teaching profession.\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2865, \"end\": 2867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"score\": 0.9999999999431566, \"rank\": 5.5245450016798584e-11, \"text\": \"PE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The letter\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2797}, {\"ngram\": \"better training\", \"from\": 2808, \"to\": 2823}, {\"ngram\": \"tools\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2833}, {\"ngram\": \"teachers\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2846}, {\"ngram\": \"more emphasis\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"the curriculum\", \"from\": 2871, \"to\": 2885}, {\"ngram\": \"a push\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2896}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2919}, {\"ngram\": \"disabled people\", \"from\": 2923, \"to\": 2938}, {\"ngram\": \"the teaching profession\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2971}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whiston's tearful post-race interview after finishing runner-up in the women's 100m SB8 breaststroke was one of the most memorable of the Games.\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2974, \"end\": 2981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"score\": 0.9999999997971827, \"rank\": 1.2310253222161583e-10, \"text\": \"Whiston\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"runner-up\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3037}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's 100m\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3057}, {\"ngram\": \"SB8 breaststroke\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3074}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3117}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paralympic debutant was utterly crushed not to win that final, even apologising for her performance.\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3224, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Paralympic debutant\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"her performance\", \"from\": 3208, \"to\": 3223}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the vulnerable, viral moment further endeared her to the British public, who flooded Whiston with encouragement on social media before she bounced back to claim her first Paralympic title.\", \"from\": 3226, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3287, \"end\": 3294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9356701769856102, \"rank\": 0.0626937378971742, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3315, \"end\": 3322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"score\": 0.9999999997971827, \"rank\": 1.2310253222161583e-10, \"text\": \"Whiston\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the vulnerable, viral moment\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3258}, {\"ngram\": \"encouragement\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3341}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 3345, \"to\": 3357}, {\"ngram\": \"her first Paralympic title\", \"from\": 3391, \"to\": 3417}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old's success in the pool contributed to an overall 32 medals for Britain's swimmers, 18 of them gold.\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3498, \"end\": 3505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8057774438914019, \"rank\": 0.2410293185794247, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 27-year-old's success\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3445}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3457}, {\"ngram\": \"an overall 32 medals\", \"from\": 3473, \"to\": 3493}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whiston's team-mate Alice Tai claimed five medals in the pool, including two Paralympic titles.\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3536, \"end\": 3543, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"score\": 0.9999999997971827, \"rank\": 1.2310253222161583e-10, \"text\": \"Whiston\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Whiston\"}, {\"begin\": 3556, \"end\": 3565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Tai\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alice Tai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Tai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Tai\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"five medals\", \"from\": 3574, \"to\": 3585}, {\"ngram\": \"the pool\", \"from\": 3589, \"to\": 3597}, {\"ngram\": \"two Paralympic titles\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tai, who could easily recall her own experiences of feeling excluded in school PE, said: \\\"I think if you are excluded it can have a massive impact.\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3633, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benny_Tai\", \"score\": 0.999999984144779, \"rank\": 1.3264325983576928e-08, \"text\": \"Tai\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benny_Tai\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Benny_Tai\"}, {\"begin\": 3712, \"end\": 3714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"score\": 0.9999999999431566, \"rank\": 5.5245450016798584e-11, \"text\": \"PE\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Physical_education\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her own experiences\", \"from\": 3662, \"to\": 3681}, {\"ngram\": \"feeling\", \"from\": 3685, \"to\": 3692}, {\"ngram\": \"a massive impact\", \"from\": 3763, \"to\": 3779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think the Paralympics proves that sport is accessible and it just takes people to have open minds, listen to people with disabilities, advocate for us, and keep everything going after the Paralympics.\", \"from\": 3782, \"to\": 3985, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 3791, \"to\": 3806}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3819, \"to\": 3824}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3863}, {\"ngram\": \"open minds\", \"from\": 3872, \"to\": 3882}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 3894, \"to\": 3900}, {\"ngram\": \"disabilities\", \"from\": 3906